 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","title":"Implement messaging and broker/client-family parity","description":"Port the messaging families that were previously bundled incorrectly into the database bead: broker/client abstractions, queue/topic/stream semantics, producer/consumer lifecycle, retries, backpressure, and shutdown behavior. Users experience these very differently from SQL clients, so they need their own acceptance contract.","design":"Treat messaging as a distinct reliability surface with ordering, delivery, retry, visibility timeout, and shutdown semantics. Require detailed logs and retained evidence for dropped/retried/poisoned message flows rather than collapsing them into generic transport tests.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public messaging client/broker families are represented explicitly with documented semantics and unsupported-case policy.\nB. Unit/integration tests cover queue/topic lifecycle, producer/consumer failure handling, retry/backpressure, and shutdown/drain behavior.\nC. Logged e2e scenarios capture message flow, retries, poison/failure handling, and artifact-rich summaries.","notes":"Upstream references: messaging-related exports and any queue/broker abstractions outside the database family. This bead exists because bd-yx9r.11.1 should stay focused on database semantics.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:48.466723429Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["broker","crate-parity","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:40.388907539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:48.465842472Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:41.212117320Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:42.055118237Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:46.533361627Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:47.473387985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.12","title":"Developer, operator, and acceptance-surface parity","description":"The upstream crate includes user/operator-facing surfaces beyond runtime APIs: CLI/console, tracing compatibility, test internals, examples, and a broader parity story across docs and smoke packs. The ANSI C port needs comparable operator/developer affordances if it is claiming real functional parity.","design":"This epic captures the non-kernel, non-protocol surfaces that determine whether the port is practically usable and supportable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. CLI/console/test-helper/examples/docs surfaces are represented explicitly.\\nB. Final crate-level acceptance is backed by logged smoke packs and an auditable parity report.\\nC. The backlog no longer treats docs/examples/operator flows as optional polish.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/console.rs, src/bin/asupersync.rs, src/test_*.rs, README examples, and module-specific operator flows.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:49.808248302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:35.129782549Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["acceptance","cli","conformance","core-parity","crate-parity","docs","e2e"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:49.808248302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:21.139278268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:22.270401342Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:23.383751974Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","title":"Implement CLI, console, tracing-compat, and test-internals parity","description":"Port the user-facing and developer-facing helpers that are publicly exported or shipped upstream: CLI/console entry points, tracing compatibility hooks, test logging/NDJSON/test utility surfaces, and comparable diagnostics for running the system.","design":"This should produce real operator entry points and test-support modules, not just docs stubs.","acceptance_criteria":"A. CLI/console/tracing-compat/test-internals public surfaces exist with clear build/profile gates.\\nB. Tests cover logging/report formats, CLI error handling, and tracing compatibility behavior.\\nC. Smoke packs exercise the operator path with detailed logs and rerun guidance.","notes":"Depends on A2 and A3, plus lower-level runtime/service work as needed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:51.488592152Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:03:44.659837426Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T22:03:44.659359020Z","close_reason":"Completed: shipped app/operator surface plus console/tracing-compat/test-log parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","console","crate-parity","test-internals"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:35.418742220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:51.488592152Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:04.137634865Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:37.053670038Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","title":"Build reopened-surface examples, walkthroughs, and smoke packs","description":"The reopened gap set needs canonical examples and smoke packs for the new module families just as much as the earlier kernel/browser/native work did. Otherwise parity claims will outpace usability and regression detection.","design":"Create curated examples and deterministic smoke packs that cover the major newly reopened surfaces: service/transport, network, HTTP/web, gRPC, database/messaging, distributed, CLI/operator flows, and capability/security cases.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Example set covers each major reopened family with concrete, runnable scenarios.\\nB. Smoke scripts emit JSONL logs, summaries, artifact manifests, and replay/rerun hints.\\nC. The examples are validated so they do not silently rot when APIs change.","notes":"Depends on A3 and the relevant implementation epics.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:53.213129144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-17T01:47:27.197902894Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","examples","smoke"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:38.134282323Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:53.213129144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:39.227947546Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:05.457302721Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","title":"Build reopened-surface examples, walkthroughs, and smoke packs","description":"The reopened gap set needs canonical examples and smoke packs for the new module families just as much as the earlier kernel/browser/native work did. Otherwise parity claims will outpace usability and regression detection.","design":"Create curated examples and deterministic smoke packs that cover the major newly reopened surfaces: service/transport, network, HTTP/web, gRPC, database/messaging, distributed, CLI/operator flows, and capability/security cases.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Example set covers each major reopened family with concrete, runnable scenarios.\\nB. Smoke scripts emit JSONL logs, summaries, artifact manifests, and replay/rerun hints.\\nC. The examples are validated so they do not silently rot when APIs change.","notes":"Depends on A3 and the relevant implementation epics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:53.213129144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T02:11:37.924871921Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T02:11:37.924282406Z","close_reason":"Example coverage now spans all implemented reopened surfaces. Added ex_encoding_decoding.c (4 scenarios, 17 checks: roundtrip, max-frame, cancellation, lines codec) and ex_evidence_monitoring.c (4 scenarios, 17 checks: healthy monitor, watchdog violation, observability snapshot, evidence helpers). Combined with existing examples (quickstart, channel, cancel, timeout, lab, browser, network, actor_supervision), all major implemented families have curated examples with SCENARIO/ARTIFACT output for smoke validation. Remaining families (HTTP, gRPC, distributed, database) are blocked on unimplemented subsystems.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","examples","smoke"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:38.134282323Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:53.213129144Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:39.227947546Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:05.457302721Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","title":"Define and enforce the final crate-level parity acceptance gate","description":"The old closure problem happened because the acceptance story stopped at kernel semantics. This task defines the final gate that decides whether ANSI C has truly replicated the core functionality of /dp/asupersync at the crate level or still has declared exclusions.","design":"The gate should aggregate the reopened inventory, feature/platform matrix, unit and invariant evidence, scenario and end-to-end smoke packs, detailed structured logs, retained artifacts, and any remaining justified exclusions into one auditable release-quality decision.","acceptance_criteria":"A. There is a single crate-level acceptance artifact or protocol that enumerates what is implemented, what is explicitly deferred, and what evidence supports each claim.\nB. The gate fails if public-export families remain silently absent or only stubbed without recorded exclusion.\nC. The gate requires comprehensive unit coverage plus logged e2e scenario/script evidence with retained artifacts for every crate-level family.\nD. The final report is detailed enough that a reviewer can decide parity status without reopening the original plans or upstream source tree.","notes":"This is the terminal blocker for the new root epic and must explicitly include the newer data-plane and actor/supervision tracks as part of parity truth.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:54.995583252Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:57.938417444Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["acceptance","crate-parity","gating"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:40.894345997Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:17.379440146Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:19.348962693Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:54.995583252Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:20.774761578Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:22.214882448Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.18","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:55.956658375Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.19","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:56.984364499Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:42.055448511Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:43.210095869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:07.040952636Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:08.673186421Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:10.332082111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:12.113331493Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:13.713303668Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:15.365734795Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.13","title":"Combinator, service, transport, remote, and spork parity","description":"Upstream asupersync exports high-level orchestration families that sit on top of runtime/networking foundations: combinators, service layers, transport adapters, remote helpers, link/session surfaces, and spork-style execution tools. ANSI C currently lacks most of this public orchestration layer.","design":"This epic should make the C port feel like a usable async framework rather than only a kernel plus scattered protocol pieces.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Higher-level orchestration surfaces exist with explicit cancellation/outcome behavior.\\nB. Tests cover composition semantics, buffering/rate limits/timeouts/retries, and failure propagation.\\nC. Protocol/application layers can build on these APIs instead of inventing ad hoc wrappers.","notes":"Primary upstream references: combinator exports in src/lib.rs, src/service/*, src/transport/*, remote-related exports, src/spork, src/link.rs, and session-related surfaces.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:14.287586776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:40.382725357Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:40.379473997Z","close_reason":"Superseded by earlier canonical reopened parity backlog issues under bd-yx9r.7 through bd-yx9r.12","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity","service","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.13","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:14.287586776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.13.1","title":"Port join/race/select/timeout/retry combinator surface","description":"ANSI C needs the real user-facing combinator layer promised by the upstream crate, not just ad hoc kernel helpers. This includes joins, races, selection, timeout wrappers, retry-ish composition, and explicit outcome aggregation semantics.","design":"Implement the combinators as stable public APIs with strong cancellation and ownership contracts, backed by law-style tests and realistic composition scenarios.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public combinator APIs exist and integrate with Outcome, cancellation, and scope rules.\\nB. Unit/property tests cover algebraic composition and loser-drain behavior.\\nC. Smoke scenarios demonstrate real multi-branch orchestration with detailed logs.","notes":"Depends on B and D.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:17.469048894Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:30.818613228Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:42:30.818022487Z","close_reason":"Superseded by earlier canonical reopened parity backlog issues under bd-yx9r.7 through bd-yx9r.12","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.13.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.13","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:17.469048894Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
