-{"id":"bd-yx9r.18","title":"Data-plane, decoding, encoding, I/O, and RaptorQ parity","description":"The reopened backlog was still missing a dedicated track for upstream data-plane families: decoding, encoding, io, raptorq, and related migration/interop helpers. Those modules are exported directly by the Rust crate and materially affect real user workflows.","design":"Treat this as the user-visible data-path epic: buffer/codec usage is not enough by itself. The plan should cover public decoding/encoding pipelines, async I/O adapter contracts, erasure-coding surfaces, and compatibility/migration helpers with strong test evidence and detailed logs.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Decoding/encoding/io/raptorq families are represented explicitly as public ANSI C work.\\nB. Unit plus integration/e2e evidence requirements are defined for data-plane correctness, failure handling, and artifact logging.\\nC. Higher protocol and distributed/database tracks can depend on this epic rather than re-describing data-path gaps.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/decoding.rs, src/encoding.rs, io-related exports, raptorq exports, and migration-related exports in src/lib.rs.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:53.977697245Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:14.790343011Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","decoding","encoding","io","raptorq"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.18","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:53.977697245Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.18","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:12.164927028Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.18","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:13.479007031Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id"