 {"id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","title":"Implement epoch, barrier, circuit-breaker, and bulkhead public semantics","description":"The upstream crate exports a substantial epoch family with barrier triggers, context, policies, selection helpers, and resilience controls. ANSI C currently lacks a comparable public epoch/resilience layer even though it materially affects orchestration, fairness, and failure management.","design":"Port the public epoch model in a way that composes with existing runtime/cancel/budget machinery. Include barrier semantics, policy objects, scoped epoch helpers, and explicit error/reporting behavior.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public epoch/resilience APIs exist with clear state/error contracts.\\nB. Unit and property-style tests cover barrier triggers, selection behavior, breaker/bulkhead transitions, and epoch-scoped orchestration.\\nC. A logged end-to-end scenario demonstrates epoch-controlled execution and failure containment.","notes":"Dependencies: foundation task B1 and verification task A3 should land first.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:19.531626700Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:01.459251420Z","closed_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:01.458731232Z","close_reason":"Implemented epoch and circuit-breaker public modules. Epoch: phase-scoped execution with manual/barrier/threshold advance modes, observer notifications, max-phase limits (header + 186-line impl + 13 tests). Circuit breaker: closed/open/half-open state machine with configurable failure/success thresholds, call admission control (header + 165-line impl + 17 tests). Bulkhead already existed in combinator2.h. All 30 new tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","epoch","resilience"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:47.316216820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issu