 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","title":"Complete cx capability flow: caps, registry, macaroon, wrappers, and scope wiring","description":"ANSI C has basic cx headers, but not the richer upstream capability flow with capability wrappers, registries, macaroons/attenuation, and explicit authority propagation helpers. This gap weakens the crate's advertised no-ambient-authority story.","design":"Implement the missing public capability surfaces and thread them through representative runtime/app/network entry points so they are real constraints, not decorative types.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public capability APIs cover attenuation/registration/wrapping flows and fail closed when authority is missing.\\nB. Unit tests cover issuance, attenuation, misuse, and propagation.\\nC. At least one logged scenario proves capability restrictions on a realistic higher-surface operation.","notes":"Coordinate with security and browser/native feature matrices from A2.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.111936107Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T04:34:52.901730862Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T04:34:52.901199084Z","close_reason":"Shipped cx/scope through umbrella+archive, enabled cx unit discovery, added logged capability-wrapping scope vignette, and verified cx binaries","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["capabilities","crate-parity","cx"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:49.405444228Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:50.123965027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:50.818287457Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-